This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes two algorithms for solving the cascading bandits problem using linear generalization. It also involves online learning, which is a common topic in the machine learning literature. 

It could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as the problem of recommending items is a common task in information retrieval. 

The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes algorithms for making intelligent recommendations. 

The use of features to predict attraction probabilities of items suggests that this paper could also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper proposes practical learning algorithms, which could fall under the computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
